{{Use mdy dates|date = January 2016}} {{Infobox person |image = SDCC 2015 - Colton Dunn (19047506394).jpg |caption = Dunn at the 2015 [[Comic-Con International]] |birthname = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1977|06|30}} |birth_place = [[Normal, Illinois]], U.S. |residence = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S. |education = |alma_mater = |occupation = Writer, actor, comedian, producer |yearsactive = 2001–present |networth = |spouse = |children = |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Colton Dunn''' (born June 30, 1977) is an American comedian, actor, writer, and producer. He is best known for his work on the [[Comedy Central]] sketch comedy series ''[[Key & Peele]]'' (2013–2015), where he served as writer, producer, and an occasional performer throughout its five-season run.<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Kavner|first1 = Lucas|title = Key and Peele’s Head Writers Pick Their Top 10 Keegan-Michael Key and Jordan Peele Performances|url = http://www.vulture.com/2015/07/key-and-peele-head-writers-top-kp-performances.html|website = Vulture|accessdate = January 17, 2016}}</ref> Dunn also played Herman in ''[[Lazer Team]]'' (2015) and [[Lazer Team 2|its sequel]] (2017).
==Life and career== Born in 1977 in Normal, Illinois, Dunn moved to St. Paul, Minnesota, with his mother, when he was a toddler. While attending St. Paul Central High School, he was involved in theater and joined an improv comedy group. Dunn moved to New York in 1998, and while there, worked for ''[[Late Night with Conan O'Brien]]''. He then moved to Los Angeles in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gustafson|first1=Amy Carlson|title=St. Paul Central grad Colton Dunn could go big this year with TV series, movie|url=http://www.twincities.com/2015/12/31/st-paul-central-grad-colton-dunn-could-go-big-this-year-with-tv-series-movie/|website=twincities.com|accessdate=September 21, 2016}}</ref>
Prior to working on ''Key & Peele'', Dunn was a writer and performer on ''[[Mad TV|madTV]]'', from 2005 to 2009.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Meehan|first1=Ryan|title=7 Questions with Colton Dunn|url=http://firstorderhistorians.com/2015/02/04/7-questions-with-colton-dunn/|website=First Order Historians|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref> He has also appeared in ''[[Parks and Recreation]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Evans|first1 = Bradford|title = 10 ‘Parks and Rec’ Writers Who Have Played Characters on the Show|url = http://splitsider.com/2014/01/10-parks-and-rec-writers-who-have-played-characters-on-the-show/|website = [[Splitsider]]|accessdate = January 17, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Nick Swardson's Pretend Time]]'', ''Game Shop'', ''[[Burning Love (TV series)|Burning Love]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Colton Dunn Joins NBC Pilot ‘The Pro’|url=http://deadline.com/2014/02/colton-dunn-joins-nbc-pilot-the-pro-jonathan-tucker-in-directv-series-navy-st-681095/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref> a small part on College Humor's "If Google Was a Guy" and currently co-stars in ''[[Superstore (TV series)|Superstore]]'' on [[NBC]].<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Lee|first1 = Ben|title = NBC's Superstore comedy pilot adds Colton Dunn and two more|url = http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ustv/news/a632834/nbcs-superstore-comedy-pilot-adds-colton-dunn-and-two-more/|website = [[Digital Spy]]|accessdate = January 17, 2016}}</ref> Dunn hosted the comedy variety show ''RT-ES'', produced by [[Rooster Teeth Productions]], and co-starred in their sci-fi action comedy ''[[Lazer Team]]'' in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Splangler|first1 = Todd|title = Fullscreen’s Rooster Teeth Finally Goes Mobile|url = https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/rooster-teeth-mobile-apps-lazer-team-1201590871/|website = ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''|accessdate = January 17, 2016}}</ref>
He is an alumnus of the [[improvisational comedy]] group [[Boom Chicago]] and has performed and taught at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade]] [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre|Theatre]] since 1999.<ref>{{cite web|title=Colton Dunn - UCB|url=http://ucbcomedy.com/user/2709|publisher=[[Upright Citizens Brigade]]|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref>
Dunn has received two [[Emmy Award]] nominations for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series|Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series]] for his work on ''Key & Peele''.<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Staff|first1 = THR|title = Emmy Awards: The Complete Winners List|url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/emmy-winners-2015-complete-results-825450/item/lead-actor-a-drama-series-825568|website = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate = January 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title = Colton Dunn bio|url = http://www.emmys.com/bios/colton-dunn|website = Emmys.com|publisher = [[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate = January 17, 2016}}</ref>
