'''Shakira Martin''' (June 1, 1986 – August 3, 2016) was a [[Jamaicans|Jamaican]] model and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned [[Miss Jamaica Universe|Miss Jamaica Universe 2011]] and represented [[Jamaica]] at [[Miss Universe 2011]] in [[Brazil]] on September 12, 2011.

==Early life and career==
Martin was born on June 1, 1986, in [[Brooklyn, New York]]. Her family relocated to South Florida in 1989, but would visit her mother's homeland of [[Jamaica]] frequently. She was a student of [[Nova High School]] and graduated in 2004. She then attended [[Broward College]].<ref name="sun">{{cite news|last1=Huriash|first1=Lisa|title=Shakira Martin, 2011 Miss Jamaica Universe, dies at 30|url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/local/broward/fl-shakira-martin-obit-20160804-story.html|accessdate=5 August 2016|work=Sun Sentinel|publisher=Sun Sentinel}}
</ref> Before becoming a model, Martin was a pre-school teacher.<ref name="gleaner">{{cite news|last1=Hayles|first1=Olivea|title=Shakira Martin is Committed|url=http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20110728/ent/ent3.html|accessdate=5 August 2016|work=The Gleaner|agency=The Gleaner Company|date=July 28, 2011}}</ref>
Martin competed in a pageant in Miami and came in second. A friend of Martin's convinced her to compete in Miss Jamaica Universe.<ref name=sun /> Martin won the title of Miss Jamaica Universe in 2011 and used her crown as a platform to raise awareness for people affected by [[sickle cell anemia]].<ref name=gleaner /> in 2011, Martin was a part of a toy drive that donated 400 toys to ill children in a Jamaican hospital.<ref name=sun /> She had modeled in several different countries such as Jamaica, Brazil, Canada and Haiti.<ref name=loop />

Martin was diagnosed with sickle cell anemia at 3 months old.<ref name=loop>{{cite news|last1=Riley|first1=Gavin|title=Former Miss Jamaica Universe Shakira Martin has died|url=http://www.loopjamaica.com/content/former-miss-jamaica-universe-shakira-martin-has-died|accessdate=5 August 2016|work=Loop Jamaica|agency=Trend Media|date=August 2, 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805000110/http://www.loopjamaica.com/content/former-miss-jamaica-universe-shakira-martin-has-died|archivedate=5 August 2016|df=}}</ref> Both of Martin's parents had the trait for the disease and thus had a 25 percent chance of giving it to a child. Her brother is also a carrier of the trait.<ref name="ja">{{cite news|last1=Wilson|first1=Nadine|title=Miss Ja Universe's sickle cell fight|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/magazines/allwoman/Miss-Ja-Universe-s-sickle-cell-fight_9221247|accessdate=5 August 2016|work=All Woman|agency=Jamaican Observer|date=July 18, 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806065723/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/magazines/allwoman/Miss-Ja-Universe-s-sickle-cell-fight_9221247|archivedate=6 August 2016|df=}}</ref>

==Death==
According to Martin's mother, Martin wasn't feeling well after a trip to Jamaica.<ref name=sun /> She died at 12:28&nbsp;a.m. from complications with sickle cell blood clots in both her lungs.<ref name="gleaner2">{{cite news|last1=Henry|first1=Davina|title=Shakira Was Never A Slave To Her Disease, Says Mother Of Former Miss Ja Universe|url=http://jamaica-gleaner.com/article/news/20160803/shakira-was-never-slave-her-disease-says-mother-former-miss-ja-universe|accessdate=5 August 2016|work=The Gleaner|agency=The Gleaner Company|date=August 3, 2016}}</ref><ref name="observe">{{cite news|title=Miss Ja Universe 2011 dies from sickle cell|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/Former-Miss-Ja-Universe-loses-sickle-cell-battle|accessdate=5 August 2016|work=Jamaican Observer|agency=Jamaican Observer|date=August 3, 2016}}</ref> She was 30 years old.<ref name=gleaner />

